Passenger46975 wrote a review Apr 2019
Shanghai, China21 contributions11 helpful votes
Clean rooms, lovely staff, serious noise problem
The staff at this hotel were very pleasant - from those helping to book sightseeing visits on the ground floor to the kitchen and restaurant staff at breakfast. Everyone welcomed you with a smile and warmth that you associate with Vietnam. The room we had was spacious, well-kept and clean. The beds were very comfortable. The hotels’ location was right opposite the beach. The roof top pool and bar overlooked this beach (with only the unfortunate sight of cranes on the next door building visible - but this was not really a problem) The real problem was the noise coming from the beach and this was a serious problem. Until late at night - 11pm even later - a KTV tent blares music out at such a volume it is impossible to sleep. Not only that, at around 5am in the morning it…
