Xin chao Passenger46975, First of all, thank you very much for your recent stay with us, and taking the time to provide us with your feedback. I would like to express my most sincere apologies for your unpleasant experience and, I was very disappointed to read of your experience during your stay with us. Whilst an apology will regrettably not after the outcome of your occasion, I do extend it with all sincerity. We value all of our guests and will try our utmost to extend our usual warm and caring service at all times. Each and every associate at A La Carte Da Nang Beach is fully trained to provide dedicated service excellence but regrettably, we seem to have fallen short of our usual high standards on this occasion. I certainly empathize regarding the points you mention in your review, especially the noise you experience of the building next to our hotel Please accept my apologies for the shortfalls and please rest assured that the matter has been discussed with our relative department to ensure that we provide you with a better level of service next time you visit us. Sincerely,
Alex D wrote a review Apr 2019
Hanoi, Vietnam692 contributions96 helpful votes
Great location but need some more improvement
Beach front hotel, great location. There are a lot of restaurants around the hotel. Easy to access to the beach. The room is spacious. There is a kitchen but actually it takes up some spaces as most of the guests just stay there for few nights and no one will do any cooking there. The bathroom is dark and the shower is leaking. Breakfast is simple, not many choices for a 4 star hotel. Anyway the staff is nice and friendly
